quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,151,"Verily, it is of their falsehood that they (Quraish pagans) say:"
  37,152,""
  37,153,"Has He (then) chosen daughters rather than sons?"
  43,40,"Can you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) make the deaf to hear, or can you guide the blind or him who is in manifest error?"
  43,41,"And even if We take you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) away, We shall indeed take vengeance on them."
  43,42,"Or (if) We show you that wherewith We threaten them: then verily We have perfect command over them."
  44,25,"How many of gardens and springs that they [Fir‘aun’s (Pharaoh) people] left behind,"
  44,26,"And green crops (fields) and goodly places,"
  44,27,"And comforts of life wherein they used to take delight!"
  45,16,"And indeed We gave the Children of Israel the Scripture, and the understanding of the Scripture and its laws, and the Prophethood; and provided them with good things, and preferred them above the ‘Âlamîn (mankind and jinn of their time, during that period),"
  45,17,"And gave them clear proofs in matters [by revealing to them the Taurât (Torah)]. And they differed not until after the knowledge came to them, through envy among themselves. Verily, Your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection about that wherein they used to differ."
  45,18,"Then We have put you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) on a (plain) way of (Our) commandment [like the one which We commanded Our Messengers before you (i.e. legal ways and laws of the Islâmic Monotheism)]. So follow you that (Islâmic Monotheism and its laws), and follow not the desires of those who know not. (Tafsir At-Tabarî)."
  46,4,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم to these pagans): "
  46,5,"And who is more astray than one who calls on (invokes) besides Allâh, such as will not answer him till the Day of Resurrection, and who are (even) unaware of their calls (invocations) to them?{1}",footnotes:1:(V.5) See the footnote of (V.2:165).
  46,6,"And when mankind are gathered (on the Day of Resurrection), they (false deities) will become their enemies and will deny their worshipping."